The Vice President, Secretary Fudge, and Administrator Regan have been working on the issue of lead pipes and their impact on communities. They have been on a roadshow to raise awareness about this issue. The Vice President emphasizes the importance of handling this issue urgently and with a sense of speed. Three key principles are at play: equity, public health, and education. The Vice President highlights the work being done by the agencies to address this issue and emphasizes the need to prioritize it.